\begin{activity} \label{A:11.7.3} Let $S$ be the solid cone bounded by $z = \sqrt{x^2+y^2}$ and $z=3$. A picture of $S$ is shown in Figure \ref{F:11.7.Cone_ex}. In this activity we set up an iterated integral of the form
\begin{equation} \label{eq:11.7.TI_not_box}
\int_?^? \int_?^? \int_?^? \delta(x,y,z) \, dz \, dy \, dx
\end{equation}
to represent the mass of $S$ if $\delta(x,y,z)$ tells us the density of $S$ at the point $(x,y,z)$. Our job is to find the limits on the integrals.
