\begin{exercise} 
    \ba
    \item What are the limits on $z$ in the innermost integral? A slice in the $z$ direction with $x$ and $y$ fixed is pictured in Figure \ref{F:11.7.Cone_ex}. Note that at least one of these limits is not constant but depends on $x$ and $y$.



    \item The projection of the cone $S$ onto the $xy$-plane is shown in Figure \ref{F:11.7.Cone_proj}. What are the limits on the middle integral? Note that at least one of these limits is not constant and depends on $x$.



    \item Write an iterated integral of the form (\ref{eq:11.7.TI_not_box}) that represents the mass of the cone $S$.



    \ea

